# Troubleshooting GRSK_MKP1593

The mitogenome of GRSK_MKP1593 was difficult to assemble due to the tandemly duplicated region. It took three times in order to retrieve contigs that could be stitched together without any gaps or missing sequence.
Here is the process I used:

1) I ran NOVOPlasty with ND1 as the seed, NOVOPlasty incorrectly circularized it and skipped over the first copy of the duplication. I know that there should be a second duplicate based on the raw sequencing reads.
Here is the part that I was able to assemble, note the big gap in the middle where the first duplicate should be:
